Eastwick is offering a wonderful opportunity to Paterson residents with a high school diploma or GED through this training grant. You will be provided with 600 hours of on-campus training in plumbing, heating, carpentry, and more! At the end of the training, you will receive on-the-job, part-time employment with the City of Paterson.

For full details and requirements, contact HoHoKus School of Trade at 800-646-WELD or visit hohokus.edu/info.

post_text:
National History Day is a nation-wide competition that challenges middle and high school students to discover and experience history for themselves. Kean University hosted the Eastern Regionals on 3/18/17. Students from across the region put together exhibits, posters, videos, theatrical presentations, etc. They are then judged by panels to see who advances on to the next level.
We are pleased to announce that two of our students qualified for state level competition! We want to congratulate all the students who competed for their outstanding efforts. Wishing our students continuous success at the state level!!!

We are pleased to announce that two of our students qualified for state level competition! We want to congratulate all the students who competed for their outstanding efforts. Wishing our students continuous success at the state level!!!

Also a very special thank you to the Gilder Lehrman American History Foundation for this phenomenal opportunity!!!
